content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> <!-- JNLP File for Cockpit -->  <jnlp      codebase="http://www.eol.ucar.edu/software/webstart/cockpit/javaws"     href="cockpit.jnlp"     version="1.0">     <information>         <title> Cockpit </title>         <vendor> National Center for Atmospheric Research (NCAR)</vendor>         <description>             A thumbnail display program to show realtime sensor data and status. The             program connects to a data server remotely or locally, gets data for each             measurement through network socket, and displays the current data on a             plot, and colors the current data to diffirent color as a histroy trace, so             that the plot show the history and current measurement data.         </description>         <homepage href="http://www.eol.ucar.edu/software/webstart/cockpit/index.html"/>         <description kind="short">Sensor measurement display program</description>         <icon href="image/nodata.png" />         <offline-allowed/>     </information>     <!--         Since nativelibs are part of the package, then must specify all-permissions     -->     <security>  <all-permissions/>     </security>     <resources>              <jar href="cockpit.jar"  main="true"    download="eager" />         <package name="edu.ucar.nidas.apps.cockpit.ui.*" part="cockpit" recursive="true"/>         <jar href="lib/qtjambi-4.5.0_01.jar"/>         <jar href="lib/serializer.jar"/>     </resources>      <resources os='Windows' arch='x86'>         <jar href="lib/win/qtjambi-win32-msvc2005-4.5.0_01.jar"/>         <j2se version="1.5+" />     </resources>      <resources os='Windows' arch='x86_64'>         <jar href="lib/win/qtjambi-win32-msvc2005-4.5.0_01.jar"/>         <j2se version="1.5+" />     </resources>      <resources os='Linux' arch='i386'>      <jar href="lib/linux/qtjambi-linux32-gcc-4.5.0_01.jar"/>         <j2se version="1.5+" />     </resources>      <!-- os should match java.lang.System.getProperty("os.name"), and arch should     match property "os.arch".  On 64 bit RedHat EL5 and Fedora systems,     os.arch is "amd64" (even on intel processors) -->     <resources os='Linux' arch='amd64'>         <jar href="lib/linux/qtjambi-linux64-gcc-4.5.0_01.jar"/>         <j2se version="1.5+" />     </resources>      <resources os='Mac' >         <jar href="lib/mac/qtjambi-macosx-gcc-4.5.0_01.jar"/>         <!-- Only arguments regarded as safe by the receiving system will be passed              to the java-vm. Right now it appears that -XstartOnFirstThread isn't regarded as safe -->         <j2se version="1.6" java-vm-args="-d32 -XstartOnFirstThread"/>     </resources>      <application-desc main-class="edu.ucar.nidas.apps.cockpit.ui.CockPit">     </application-desc> </jnlp>
